**Elasticsearch version** (`bin/elasticsearch --version`): reported in 7.9 and reproduced with master (98943a28bef8a66014ce9a32ba37e0b8864b1d2c)

**Plugins installed**: reproduces with `./gradlew :x-pack:plugin:core run`

**JVM version** (`java -version`): Java 16

**OS version** (`uname -a` if on a Unix-like system): reproduced with
```
Linux beast 5.12.10-arch1-1 #1 SMP PREEMPT Thu, 10 Jun 2021 16:34:50 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux
```

**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:
Simulating a watch that contains a `search` followed by an `index` action runs the action for real.

**Steps to reproduce**:

```
curl -ux_pack_rest_user:x-pack-test-password -XDELETE localhost:9200/my-index
curl -ux_pack_rest_user:x-pack-test-password -HContent-Type:application/json -XPUT localhost:9200/_watcher/watch/badguy?pretty -d'{
  "trigger": {
    "schedule": {
      "interval": "3d"
    }
  },
  "input": {
    "search": {
      "request": {
        "search_type": "query_then_fetch",
        "indices": [
          "*"
        ],
        "rest_total_hits_as_int": true,
        "body": {
          "size": 0,
          "query": {
            "match_all": {}
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "condition": {
    "compare": {
      "ctx.payload.hits.total": {
        "gte": 10
      }
    }
  },
  "actions": {
    "index_payload": {
      "transform": {
        "script": {
          "source": "\ndef docs = [];\n            docs.add([\n                          \"fieldOne\": \"aaaaaaaa\"\n            ]);\n            return [\"_doc\": docs]\n            ",
          "lang": "painless"
        }
      },
      "index": {
        "index": "my-index"
      }
    }
  }
}'
curl -ux_pack_rest_user:x-pack-test-password -HContent-Type:application/json -XPOST localhost:9200/_watcher/watch/badguy/_execute?pretty -d'{
  "trigger_data" : { 
     "triggered_time" : "now",
     "scheduled_time" : "now"
  },
  "alternative_input" : { 
    "foo" : "bar"
  },
  "ignore_condition" : true, 
  "action_modes" : {
    "index_payload" : "simulate" 
  },
  "record_execution" : true 
}'

curl -ux_pack_rest_user:x-pack-test-password localhost:9200/_cat/indices
# Oh no! my-index is there!
curl -ux_pack_rest_user:x-pack-test-password localhost:9200/my-index/_search?pretty
# Oh no! The simulated doc is there!
```

commit_message:
Fix testPersistentCacheCleanUpAfterRelocation (#74481)

The test SearchableSnapshotsPersistentCacheIntegTests 
testPersistentCacheCleanUpAfterRelocation rarely fails 
after the snapshot is mounted for the first time and the 
test waits for the persistent cache to have at least 1 doc:

if (indicesService.hasIndex(mountedIndex)) {
     assertBusy(() -> {
     CacheService cacheService = internalCluster().getInstance(...);
     cacheService.synchronizeCache();

>>>     assertThat(cacheService.getPersistentCache().getNumDocs(), greaterThan(0L));
     dataNodes.add(node);
      });
}

This situation happens when a low number of docs are 
ndexed and one (or more) of the 3 shards receive no 
documents.

This commit changes the test to index more documents 
(1K+) so that all shards have documents, and thus 
cache files to synchronize and to make persistent in 
the persistent cache.

Closes #74360

